AUDIENCE: Second of all, you're
all so casually talking

00:50:30.620 --> 00:50:31.305
about auditioning.

00:50:31.305 --> 00:50:33.760
And in the corporate world, it's
like, oh, I'm tiptoeing

00:50:33.760 --> 00:50:35.990
out at lunch hour to
go on an interview.

00:50:35.990 --> 00:50:38.950
So is it very normal for you
to just be auditioning for

00:50:38.950 --> 00:50:41.256
other projects while you're
working on this?

00:50:41.256 --> 00:50:42.460
SANTINO FONTANA: Well, they're
all different.

00:50:42.460 --> 00:50:44.420
I mean, the audition I was
talking about the other day,

00:50:44.420 --> 00:50:45.950
they're voiceovers.

